BY STAFF REPORTER Former Zimbabwe Republic Police deputy commissioner Moses Griffiths Mpofu has been declared a national hero. He was 66. Zanu PF spokesperson Simon Khaya Moyo confirmed the development last night. Khaya Moyo said the politburo had unanimously declared the late Mpofu a national hero in recognition of his role in the liberation of this country. Mpofu, whose Chimurenga name was Matswata Witness Mhlanga, died last Friday at United Bulawayo Hospital after a long illness.